body:
I have a hunch in which direction this might go.

The `HonoClientImpl` is dependent on the information of `isConnected()`, which it implements by using `isDisconnected()` from `ProtonConnection`. Which implements this in `ProtonConnectionImpl` as:

~~~java
public boolean isDisconnected() {
   return transport == null;
}
~~~

However a call to `ProtonConnection#disconnect()` does:

~~~java
public void disconnect() {
    if (transport != null) {
      transport.disconnect();
    }
}
~~~

So calling `disconnect()` and then `isDisconnected()` should still return `false`, as the transport still is non-null.

I will try to test this tomorrow.
